Someone who bought a lottery ticket in Pretoria is R57.7 million richer after winning Friday night s mega Ithuba PowerBall jackpot. The lucky winner who on Saturday had yet to come forward and claim their winnings played for R45 and made a selection of five numbers and a PowerBall to become the country s latest multi-millionaire. The winning ticket was purchased in the nation s capital on the day of the draw. This week also saw a PowerBall Plus player from the south of Johannesburg walking away with just over R25.7 million and a KwaZulu-Natal player winning the R33.3 million LOTTO jackpot. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share